text: The EmsAuenWeg is a 115 kilometer long-distance cycle path in Münsterland opened in 2004. The EmsAuenWeg leads past the middle Ems over the village Telgte at Münster. It follows the path of the Rheine through Greven, Saerbeck, and Emsdetten. The path is parallel to railroad lines. ==External links== * EmsAuenWeg Category:Cycling in Germany Category:Cycleways in Germany Category:Münster (region)
